&lt;p&gt;LONDON&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UCLH NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Specialist Dietitian - Nutrition Team &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1.00wte (37.5 hours a week) Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fixed Term Contract for 6 months&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Provisional interview date: TBC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you keen to join a specialist and innovative team?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to maternity leave we are looking for a dynamic Dietitian with existing experience and specialist knowledge of parenteral nutrition to work within the Trust multidisciplinary Nutrition Team. This is a fantastic opportunity to gain experience in an expanding Intestinal Failure centre working with an experienced and established team and alongside a rotational band 6 Dietitian. You should have strong leadership skills, audit and research experience, ability to work effectively within teams and be able to manage your time effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team has a strong research ethos and an interest in research and audit, as well as education and training is pivotal to this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a forward thinking Nutrition and Dietetics Service, committed to clinical governance initiatives. You will be actively involved in CPD and department activities to support your professional registration and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, please contact Ian Taylor, Head of Nutrition &amp; Dietetics, Tel: 020 3447 9159 or via ian.taylor10@nhs.net or Niamh Keane, Senior Specialist Dietitian via N.Keane@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
